&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospital of North Midlands&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Stoke University Hospital &amp; County Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directorate of Obstetrics and Gynaecology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Training Fellow in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for 1 fixed term post for 10 months for an Advanced Training Fellow Doctor in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology to start immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic Advanced Training Fellow in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology. This post will provide an excellent chance to further develop your skills in both Obstetrics and/or Gynaecology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The department has a strong reputation in numerous areas such Urogynaecology, Gynae-oncology, Fetal Medicine, Ambulatory Gynaecology and an Endometriosis Centre as well as a centre of excellence for both undergraduate and postgraduate education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The department’s gynaecological and obstetric practice is diverse. Emergency gynaecology services and early pregnancy unit are supervised through the on-call Gynaecologist as well as the Gynaecologist of the Morning. Daily clinical responsibilities will include both Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology. You will be covering Labour Ward, Gynae wards, outpatient clinics, inpatient and day case theatre sessions and Antenatal clinics. The post will be part of the 1:10 senior registrar On-call rota (Subject to change).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Should the candidate require continued training and assessment, we can offer the following ATSM training as post CCT:- Fetal Medicine, Maternal Medicine, Advanced Labour Ward, Labour Ward Leadership and Gynae-oncology. Other ATSMs maybe negotiable after discussion. All ATSM’s can be provided within the RCOG ATSM framework.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will join a team of 22 consultants and training doctors to provide Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology services to the local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMr M ShahinJob titleConsultant in Obstetrics and GynaecologyEmail addressMohamed.Shahin@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01782 672378&lt;/p&gt;
